163  case 6:

165  y = initCellY - xIn;
166  break;
167  case 7:

170  break;

205  bool MapStoreBeam::nextCell2(int &x, int &y) {
206 #endif
207  /*
208  * the basic equation is y = x*slope with slope = ydelta/xdelta.
209  * The problem is, we are going to use integer arithmetrics. To
210  * simplify things we assume that xdelta > ydelta, which can
211  * always be guaranteed by an appropriate coordinate
212  * transformation (basicly one or two mirroring operations). So
213  * the division and subsequent multiplication needs to be
214  * replaced by some series of addition and substraction, basicly
215  * implementing a "devision with remainder". Because we assume
216  * xdelta > ydelta we know that we will advance x by one in each
217  * step, and we will advance y by zero or one. To find the y
218  * steps, we reformulate the line equation, stating y =
219  * (x*ydelta)/xdelta. We need to advance y, whenever then
220  * integer division (x*ydelta)/xdelta changes its result. This
221  * is the case, whenever (x*ydelta) has grown by an amount of
222  * xdelta.
223  */
224 
225  if (xDelta == 0) {
226  makeMapCoord(x,y);
227  return false;
228  }
229 
230  if (yHalfStep) {
231  // continue second half-step which had to move to right *and*
232  // top. Here we do the move to top.
233  lastCellY += 1;
234  yHalfStep = false;
235  // following call set x and y according to lastCellX,Y and current octant
236  makeMapCoord(x,y);
237  return (unlimited || (lastCellX <= endX && lastCellY <= endY));
238  }
239 
240  if (xHalfStep) {
241  // perform second half-step after first one moved current
242  // position one cell up. Here we do the following move to the
243  // right and update state y2Sum.
244  y2Sum += yDelta;
245  // update y2Sum according to basic line algorithm.
246  y2Sum -= x2Delta;
247  lastCellX += 1;
248  xHalfStep = false;
249  // following call set x and y according to lastCellX,Y and current octant
250  makeMapCoord(x,y);
251  return (unlimited || (lastCellX <= endX && lastCellY <= endY));
252  }
253 
254  // first half-step
255  y2Sum += yDelta;
256  if (y2Sum > xDelta) {
257  // line crossed border to next higher y-row of cells in this
258  // first half-step. Therefore, next cell is on top of the
259  // current one, not to its side. In other words: increment y
260  // but *not* *yet* x. X will be incremented in second
261  // half-step.
262  xHalfStep = true;
263  lastCellY += 1;
264  // following call set x and y according to lastCellX,Y and current octant
265  makeMapCoord(x,y);
266  // return true;
267  return (unlimited || (lastCellX <= endX && lastCellY <= endY));
268  } else {
269  // line still in current y-row, therefore move to the right.
270  lastCellX += 1;
271  // second half-step will decide if we additionally move up.
272  }
273 
274  // second half-step
275  y2Sum += yDelta;
276  if (y2Sum > xDelta) {
277  // line crossed border to next higher y-row of cells in
278  // 2. half-step. Therefore, next cell is to the right of the
279  // current one, second-next on top of that. In other words:
280  // increment now x (done above after first half-step), and in
281  // next step unconditionaly increment y. Here we set a flag to
282  // perform second half-step at next call.
283  yHalfStep = true;
284  // update y2Sum according to basic line algorithm.
285  y2Sum -= x2Delta;
286  }
287  // following call set x and y according to lastCellX,Y and current octant
288  makeMapCoord(x,y);
289  return (unlimited || (lastCellX <= endX && lastCellY <= endY));
290  }

292 }
